    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> fitzgen submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13330#pullrequestreview-4275048064\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 594651686,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778611063
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> fitzgen created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13330#discussion_r3228795414\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Usually we return an <code>Err</code>, not panic, in this scenario in our public API. Is this a pre-existing? If so, fine to fix here or in a follow-up PR or file a follow-up issue. If not, I don't think we should diverge from the typical behavior here, unless we have a really good reason.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 594651687,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778611063
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> fitzgen created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13330#discussion_r3228819321\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>An <code>ExnRef</code> should <em>always</em> be non-null (assuming we are still in its rooting scope) because it should represent <code>(ref exn)</code> (and <code>Option&lt;ExnRef&gt;</code> should represent <code>(ref null exn)</code>). At least, that's how it is with <code>{Array,Struct,Any,Extern,...}Ref</code>, but it is possible I missed something when reviewing <code>ExnRef</code> and if so we should file a follow-up issue to fix this.</p>\n<p>I'm curious if you are actually seeing this case...</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 594651688,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778611063
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> fitzgen created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13330#discussion_r3228833469\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I wonder if this should be a debug-assert and then we just always throw the most-recently-pending exception in release mode?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 594651689,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778611063
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> fitzgen created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13330#discussion_r3228891214\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Why this change? Seems like a step backwards, and we should always be able to cast a <code>VMExnRef</code> to a <code>VMGcRef</code> via helper methods if necessary.</p>\n</blockquote>",
