    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> alexcrichton submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13330#pullrequestreview-4276733550\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 594694966,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778625345
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13330#discussion_r3230276698\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>We've got conversions from <code>&amp;mut VMExnRef -&gt; &amp;mut VMGcRef</code>, but this is a different conversion from <code>&amp;mut Option&lt;VMExnRef&gt; -&gt; &amp;mut Option&lt;VMGcRef&gt;</code> which I don't believe we have any precedent for</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 594694967,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778625345
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>alexcrichton updated <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13330\">PR #13330</a>.</p>",
        "id": 594697013,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778626306
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> fitzgen submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13330#pullrequestreview-4277015626\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 594702662,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778629506
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> fitzgen created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13330#discussion_r3230509608\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Unless you feel strongly, I'd prefer to keep this as <code>VMExnRef</code> and add the <code>Option</code>-based helpers as necessary</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 594702663,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778629507
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>github-actions[bot] added the label <code>wasmtime:c-api</code> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13330\">PR #13330</a>.</p>",
        "id": 594733992,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778644938
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> alexcrichton submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13330#pullrequestreview-4282804293\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 594878532,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778684032
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13330#discussion_r3235240950\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Personally I'm pretty wary to add more helpers over what we already have. GC already suffers from quite a lot of code duplication which makes it difficult to change things and keep everything in-sync. Adding more conversions with more <code>unsafe</code> implementations (I don't think there's any  way to do this safely or built on existing primitives) for a small amount of what is effectively documentation I feel isn't worth it. </p>\n<p>For example I think that this would require this on every <code>VM*Ref</code> type:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">option_slot_as_gc_ref</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">slot</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Option</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">VMExnRef</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Option</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">VMGcRef</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">         </span><span class=\"c1\">// SAFETY: `Option&lt;VMExnRef&gt;` and `Option&lt;VMGcRef&gt;` have the same layout, since</span>\n<span class=\"w\">         </span><span class=\"c1\">// `VMExnRef` is `repr(transparent)` over `VMGcRef`.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">         </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">slot</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Option</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">VMExnRef</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Option</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">VMGcRef</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>On top of that we'd theoretically need the inverse as well, going from <code>&amp;mut Option&lt;VMGcRef&gt;</code> back to the typed representation eventually. On top of that most of these wouldn't be used so they'd be <code>#[expect(dead_code)]</code> or similar for now. </p>\n<p>Overall it feels like quite a lot of infrastructure for not really much benefit. This only affects one field in one location which is already named \"pending exception\" and I can touch up the documentation to clearly indicate that it needs to be a <code>VMExnRef</code>.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 594878537,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778684032
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> fitzgen submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13330#pullrequestreview-4283081649\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 594887884,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778686076
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> fitzgen created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13330#discussion_r3235476844\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Okay, that sounds fine for now. I think we can address these issues with a macro to reduce code duplication in a follow up though.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This only affects one field in one location which is already named \"pending exception\" and I can touch up the documentation to clearly indicate that it needs to be a <code>VMExnRef</code>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Can you add debug-asserts if possible too? Fine to skip if ultimately too difficult.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 594887885,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778686077
    },
